    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You blast the mind of a creature that you can see within range, attempting to shatter its intellect and personality. The target takes [[/damage 4d6 psychic]] damage and must make an [[/save intelligence]] save.</p><p>On a failed save, the creature’s INT and CHA become 1 (−5). The creature can’t cast spells, activate magic items, understand language, or communicate in any intelligible way. However, the creature can identify its friends, follow them, and even protect them.</p><p>At the end of every 30 days, the creature can repeat its save against this spell, ending the spell on a success.</p><p>The spell can also be ended by the <em>greater restoration</em>, <em>heal</em>, or <em>wish</em> spells.</p>",
